<p>Track these monthly. When a metric moves in the wrong direction, investigate immediately. Not after the next quarter.</p>
<p><strong>The 3 reports every scaling agency should run weekly:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Pipeline report:</strong> All active prospects, their stage, and expected close date</li>
<li><strong>Delivery report:</strong> All active clients, current deliverables status, and open issues</li>
<li><strong>Financial report:</strong> Revenue, projected churn, new client additions, and margin by client</li>
</ol>
<p>Our <a href="/blog/seo-reporting-guide/">SEO reporting guide</a> covers how to build client-facing reports that reduce churn. The <a href="/blog/seo-kpis-guide/">SEO KPIs guide</a> has the full breakdown of which metrics matter at each stage.</p>
